criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age d above 5;

          -  Subjects with deficiency of lung and spleen Qi;

          -  At least 2 or more allergic symptoms rhinorrhea , sneezing , nasal obstruction and
             nasal itching for a cumulative period greater than 1 hour per day. These symptoms may
             be accompanied by itchy and red eyes and tears;

          -  Positive srum IgE test;

          -  Voluntary written consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Known chronic disease such as asthma, rhinosinusitis, nasal polyposis;

          -  Known severe medical conditions, such as cardiovascular, liver or renal dysfunction,
             diabetes mellitus, cancers, cerebrovascular diseases, blood system diseases;

          -  Concomitant steroid, nonsteroidal anti inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), anticoagulant, and
             immunotherapy within past month;

          -  Impaired hematological profile and liver / renal function;

          -  Known alcohol and / or drug abuse;

          -  Known allergic history to any Chinese herbal medicines;

          -  Subjects who are pregnant or lactating.
